com.ibm.team.build.ant.task

Class TeamFetchTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • Task
      • com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.AbstractTeamBuildTask
        • com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.TeamFetchTask
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IStaticReset

    public final class TeamFetchTask
extends AbstractTeamBuildTask
    Ant task to fetch code from a team repository.

    Required attributes are listed below. Only one of workspaceUUID or workspaceName is allowed.

    • workspaceUUID - The UUID of the workspace from which to fetch code. This attribute is recommended over workspaceName because it identifies an exact workspace. Workspace names are less desirable because there can be multiple workspaces with the same name.
    • workspaceName - The name of the workspace from which to fetch code.
    • destination - The directory location in the local file system where the files should be fetched to.

    Optional attributes are:

    • buildResultUUID - If provided, this build result will be updated with the build workspace information. This enables the build workspace to be recreated at a later time from the build result. This attribute should be set on at most one invocation of this task per build. Build results cannot have more than one workspace associated with them. This task will throw an exception the build result already has a workspace associated with it.
    • maxScmContentThreads - If provided, this will update the number of simultaneous transfers the SCM content manager session should attempt at once. The ant attribute value cannot be negative.
    • loadRulesByUUID - The list of load rules that specify how to load each component. This must be given in the form: "<ComponentUUID1> <LoadRuleUUID1> <ComponentUUID2> <LoadRuleUUID2> etc...". Each UUID is to be separated by a single space.
    • loadRulesByPath - The list of load rules that specify how to load each component. This must be given in the form: "<LoadRulePath1>;<LoadRulePath2>;etc...". Each load rule path is to be separated by a semicolon. Example attribute value: "ComponentA/RootDirA/LoadRuleDir/myLoadRule.loadrule"
    • createFoldersForComponents - If true, component roots will be loaded as directories in the filesystem.
    • componentsToExcludeByUUID - The list of components by UUID that are to be excluded. Each UUID is to be separated by a single space.
    • componentsToExcludeByName - The list of components by name that are to be excluded. Each name is to be separated by a semicolon.
    • preserveFileTimestamps - If true, the timestamps associated with the files in the repository will be used as the timestamp of the files on the local disk when the files are loaded.
    • loadPolicy -Specifies the load policy for loading the repository workspace. This controls whether the load is driven exclusively by load rules or using simple load options like createFoldersForComponents and componentsToExcludeByUUID/componentsToExcludeByName.
    • componentLoadConfiguration - Specifies whether to load all components or exclude some components if loadPolicy is "useComponentLoadConfig".
    See AbstractTeamBuildTask for additional required and optional attributes.
    Since:
    0.5
